<p><strong>Scott Foresman Reading Street at Gorham Schools: A Comprehensive Guide</strong></p>
<p><strong>What is Scott Foresman Reading Street?</strong></p>
<p>Scott Foresman Reading Street is a popular reading program used in many elementary schools across the United States. It emphasizes literacy development and comprehension skills, incorporating fiction, nonfiction, and foundational reading strategies.</p>
<p><strong>Why has Gorham Schools adopted Scott Foresman Reading Street?</strong></p>
<p>Gorham Schools has carefully selected Scott Foresman Reading Street as its reading curriculum due to its research-based approach, comprehensive resources, and alignment with the state and national standards. The program's focus on phonemic awareness, phonics, fluency, vocabulary, and comprehension supports students' individual reading needs.</p>
<p><strong>What features does Scott Foresman Reading Street offer at Gorham Schools?</strong></p>
<p>The program provides a wide range of resources, including:</p>
<ul>
<li>Digital and print textbooks with engaging stories, nonfiction articles, and poems</li>
<li>Interactive online activities and games to reinforce skills</li>
<li>Assessments and progress monitoring tools to track student growth</li>
<li>Professional development opportunities for teachers to enhance their instruction</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>How can parents support their children's learning with Scott Foresman Reading Street?</strong></p>
<p>Parents play a crucial role in their children's literacy journey. Gorham Schools encourages parents to engage with the program by:</p>
<ul>
<li>Reading with their children daily and discussing the texts</li>
<li>Using the provided resources to practice skills and concepts</li>
<li>Attending school events and supporting classroom instruction</li>
<li>Communicating with teachers to stay informed about their children's progress</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Where can I find more information about Scott Foresman Reading Street at Gorham Schools?</strong></p>
<p>Families and educators can access additional information and resources about Scott Foresman Reading Street at Gorham Schools on the district website. The website includes:</p>
<ul>
<li>Program overviews and materials</li>
<li>Instructional schedules</li>
<li>Frequently asked questions</li>
<li>Contact information for teachers and administrators</li>
</ul>